Vancouver Canucks lose in overtime in Ottawa

OTTAWA ? Erik Karlsson scored 1:21 into overtime to give the Ottawa Senators a 4-3 NHL victory over the Vancouver Canucks on Sunday night.

Mike Zibanejad had two goals and two assists, David Legwand also scored and Craig Anderson stopped 30 shots for the Senators.

Ottawa rallied from three goals down to snap a five-game losing streak (0-4-1).

Radim Vrbata, Kevin Bieksa and Brad Richardson scored for Vancouver, and Eddie Lack made 41 saves.

The Senators¡¯ comeback bid started midway through the second period as Legwand scored a power-play goal with 9:07 remaining.

Zibanejad made the score 3-2 with 5:48 left in the second as he picked up his own rebound and banked it in off Yannick Weber, and then tied the score with 1:02 left in the period with a backhand past Lack.

Ottawa outshot the Canucks 22-7 in the second period and 45-33 for the game.

The third period was scoreless.

Vancouver lost 5-2 to the Maple Leafs in Toronto on Saturday night.

The Canucks have 38 points and are in second place in the Pacific Division of the Western Conference.

Anaheim leads the division with 41 points. The Ducks have won four games in a row, including a 4-3 overtime victory in Winnipeg on Sunday.

